  "The largest object in the asteroid belt is:": "",
  "The Moon, which orbits Earth and has a diameter of about 3,474 km but lies outside the belt region": "",
  "Ceres (a dwarf planet)": "",
  "Vesta, the second-largest body in the belt with a diameter of 525 km and a differentiated interior": "",
  "Pluto, a distant icy body orbiting beyond Neptune at an average distance of about 39 AU from the Sun": "",
  "Ceres, at ~940 km diameter, is the largest object in the asteroid belt and is classified as a dwarf planet.": "",
